This directory contains `webgl_data.db`, vendored from the Camoufox
project (https://github.com/daijro/camoufox) commit `main` as of
2026-05-28. The file is unmodified from upstream.

Camoufox is licensed under the **Mozilla Public License 2.0** (MPL-2.0).
The full text of MPL-2.0 is at https://www.mozilla.org/en-US/MPL/2.0/.

Upstream file path:
  pythonlib/camoufox/webgl/webgl_data.db

What it contains:
  SQLite database with one table `webgl_fingerprints` (vendor TEXT,
  renderer TEXT, win REAL, mac REAL, lin REAL, data TEXT). 33 rows
  representing captured per-(GPU, OS) WebGL fingerprints — each `data`
  field is a JSON object with separate `webGl:*` (WebGL 1.0) and
  `webGl2:*` (WebGL 2.0) sub-objects covering:
    - renderer / vendor / contextAttributes
    - supportedExtensions (the per-version list, with WebGL 1 vs 2
      semantic ordering)
    - parameters (~147 getParameter values keyed by GL enum)
    - shaderPrecisionFormats (12 entries)
    - webGl2Enabled

Why we vendor it:
  browser_oxide ships per-OS / per-GPU `GpuProfile` constants in
  `crates/stealth/src/gpu.rs`. The macOS Apple-M-family fixture was
  captured directly from real Chrome 147 on an M3 MacBook Pro
  (`tests/fixtures/chrome147/captured_macos_arm64.json`). Equivalent
  Windows+NVIDIA and Linux+Intel real captures are not available to
  us, but Camoufox bundles authoritative captures of those backends.
  vNext/07 §FIX-D2 and §FIX-D3 use this DB as the source of truth.

License compliance:
  - MPL-2.0 is on browser_oxide's allowlist via `deny.toml` (precedent:
    `adblock` for the optional blocker feature).
  - The file is unmodified; under MPL-2.0 §3 we must keep this file
    in the repository in source-available form (it is), and provide
    the upstream license + attribution (this file does).
  - Per MPL-2.0 §1.10, "Source Code Form" applies file-by-file: the
    derived `GpuProfile` constants in `gpu.rs` extract factual values
    (extension names, GLenum integers, numeric capabilities) which
    are not copyrightable subject matter, so the Rust code is NOT a
    "Modification" of the MPL-licensed work. We still attribute the
    source via doc comments at extraction sites.

If you do not wish to ship the MPL-2.0 file, set the `camoufox-webgl`
feature off in `crates/stealth/Cargo.toml`. (TODO: gate behind a Cargo
feature once the loader lands.)
